17 (iv) support money;
18 (v) nontaxable strike benefits;
19 (vi) cash public assistance and relief;
20 (vii) interest on federal, state, county, and municipal bonds; and
21 (viii) all payments received under federal social security except social security income paid directly
22 to a nursing home.
23 (b) For the purposes of this subsection (9), income is reduced by the taxpayer's basis.
24 (10) "Property tax billed" means taxes levied against the homestead, including special assessments
25 and fees but excluding penalties or interest during the claim period.
